  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for the Linux Kernel",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "\n\nThe SUSE Linux Enterprise 12 SP1 kernel was updated to fix the following two issues:\n\n- CVE-2017-5970: Remote attackers could have potentially caused a denial of service by sending\n bad IP options on a socket (bsc#1024938)\n- Fix a regression in MD RAID1 which could have caused wrong data to be read (bsc#1020048)\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
